OL,3,CScout leader on fatal trip declines to
OL,4,Canswer questions at inquest
OL,6,FA Scout leader on a trip where a
OL,7,Fteenager fell 200 feet to his death
OL,8,Fdeclined to answer a series of
OL,9,Fquestions from a lawyer representing
OL,10,Fthe boy's family at an inquest.
OL,12,FSean Glaister was the most senior
OL,13,Fleader on the expedition when Ben
OL,14,FLeonard, from Stockport, Greater
OL,15,FManchester, suffered fatal head
OL,16,Finjuries in the fall from cliffs on
OL,17,FAugust 26 2018.
OL,19,FBen, 16, was on an organised trip with
OL,20,Fthe Reddish Explorer Scouts,
OL,21,FManchester Civil Justice Centre heard.
