OL,3,CScout leader on fatal trip declines to
OL,4,Canswer questions at inquest
OL,6,FMr Glaister agreed he had not warned
OL,7,Fany of the Scouts, including Ben, not
OL,8,Fto leave the paths up the Orme and he
OL,9,Fwas not aware of the dangers of the
OL,10,Fcliff edges.
OL,12,FMr Richmond continued: "Not knowing
OL,13,Fthe risks inherent on the Orme was a
OL,14,Ffailure?"
OL,16,FMr Glaister said: "I would say it was
OL,17,Fa failure. I would expect them to do
OL,18,Fthe same route I would do, that's
OL,19,Fsignposted."
