OL,6,F"Yeh," Mr Glaister said. He added:
OL,7,F"This could have happened to any of
OL,8,Fthe leaders on any of the trips we
OL,9,Fwent on."
OL,11,FEarlier the hearing was told scout
OL,12,Fleaders were not aware of the need to
OL,13,Fcarry out written risk assessments and
OL,14,Fas the Scout Association was worried
OL,15,Fabout "reputational damage."
OL,17,FThe Scout Association for the first
OL,18,Ftime accepted responsibility for the
OL,19,Fdeath on the first day of the inquest
OL,20,Flast month, five and a half years
OL,21,Fafter Ben died.
